main event: Two bright orange-like oblong objects were observed via ground radar and visually for about 30 minutes.
interesting points: The objects were slow moving and disappeared from both radar and visual observations., A second similar object was observed by the same observer., There are indications that the sightings may be related to multiple phenomena such as satellites or asteroids reflecting sunlight., The exact course of the objects was not clear., The weather at the time of the sightings was favorable for viewing.
sighted object: two oblong objects with bright orange-like lights
witness description: Individuals observing from around the western horizon
